  "prompt": "Why is there no option to +1 Quora posts?",
  "response": "Quora actually does have an upvoting system, but it works slightly differently from other platforms. Instead of a \"+1\" button, Quora uses an \"Upvote\" feature to show appreciation for answers or posts. Users can upvote content they find helpful, interesting, or well-written. If you're not seeing the upvote option, it could be due to various reasons like:\n\n1. Using an older version of the app or website\n2. Not being logged in\n3. Account settings\n4. Platform-specific display issues\n\nIf you're experiencing difficulties with upvoting, you might want to:\n- Refresh the page\n- Log out and log back in\n- Update the Quora app or browser\n- Check your account settings",
